---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Senior DevOps and Site Reliability Engineer with 4+ years owning production Kubernetes and AWS
    infrastructure. Reduced observability spend by 35%, infrastructure costs by 40%, and incident
    response time by 75% through improved monitoring, alert design, and operational practices.
    Built Terraform-based infrastructure and GitOps workflows, focused on reliability, cost control,
    and capacity planning. Experienced in bridging SRE principles with DevOps practices to deliver
    infrastructure that enables rapid development without compromising reliability.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Work Experience</div>
  </div>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Site Reliability Engineer"
    subtitle="Groups360, Nashville, TN (Jan 2024 - Jan 2026)"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Owned production Kubernetes and AWS infrastructure supporting customer-facing services
        across multiple availability zones
      </li>
      <li>
        Migrated EKS provisioning from manual processes to Terraform infrastructure as code,
        enabling repeatable deployments and reducing disaster recovery time
      </li>
      <li>
        Analyzed six months of CPU and memory usage to right-size requests and limits, aligned
        scaling policies with workload patterns, reducing infrastructure costs by 40%
      </li>
      <li>
        Validated HPA scaling behavior with k6 load testing, identified bottlenecks, supported
        SLO compliance under peak load
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented anti-affinity rules, topology spread constraints, and multi-AZ pod distribution
        to improve resilience during node and availability zone failures
      </li>
      <li>
        Modernized readiness and liveness checks from static probes to endpoint-based health checks
        to improve failure detection accuracy
      </li>
      <li>
        Migrated Kubernetes deployments from Helm-based CI workflows to Argo CD GitOps, improving
        deployment reliability, traceability, and operational consistency
      </li>
      <li>
        Built a dedicated infrastructure cluster for CI runners and connected lower and production
        clusters to shared runners with strict security boundaries and access controls
      </li>
      <li>
        Migrated CI/CD runners from manually scaled infrastructure to autoscaling GitHub Actions
        runners using GitHub Actions Runner Controller
      </li>
      <li>
        Owned Datadog implementation, standardized logging, metrics, and APM across teams
      </li>
      <li>
        Built 30+ actionable monitors and alerting rules, integrated with Microsoft Teams for
        squad-based channels, improved signal quality for on-call response
      </li>
      <li>
        Reduced observability costs by 35% through host optimization, log ingestion controls,
        and APM retention tuning
      </li>
      <li>
        Automated management of 200+ GitHub repositories using Terraform, enforced standards
        across infrastructure and CI/CD pipelines
      </li>
      <li>
        Led incident response and post-incident reviews, improved runbooks and alert quality
        across production environments
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Site Reliability Engineer II"
    subtitle="Built Technologies, Nashville, TN (Jan 2023 - Jul 2023)"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Implemented Datadog monitoring, logging, and alerting for 40+ microservices, reducing
        incident response time by 75%
      </li>
      <li>
        Designed comprehensive monitoring strategies covering metrics, logs, and distributed
        traces to enhance observability
      </li>
      <li>
        Defined SLIs and SLOs with stakeholders to align reliability targets with product needs
        and business priorities
      </li>
      <li>
        Identified and resolved database performance bottlenecks using Datadog APM and distributed
        tracing
      </li>
      <li>
        Integrated DataDog with PagerDuty to establish a streamlined incident escalation and
        resolution process
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="QA Automation Engineer"
    subtitle="Built Technologies, Nashville, TN (Jan 2022 - Jan 2023)"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Built and scaled end-to-end test automation, reduced CI/CD cycle time by 75% through
        parallel execution and dependency optimization
      </li>
      <li>
        Established documentation standards to ensure high-quality and maintainable test
        automation code
      </li>
      <li>
        Optimized CI pipeline configuration with caching and dependency management to reduce
        build and deployment times
      </li>
      <li>
        Led proof-of-concept evaluations for new CI tooling to address inefficiencies and
        improve workflows
      </li>
      <li>
        Conducted training sessions on CI pipeline optimization and E2E testing best practices
      </li>
      <li>
        Recognized with the Built Onward Award for sustained impact and ownership
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Awards and Recognitions</div>
  </div>

  <TimeLineElement title="Built Onward Award" subtitle="Built Technologies, Dec 2022">
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
      <li>
        Recognized for exceptional work ethic and outstanding results, awarded to less than
        10% of team members for sustained impact and ownership
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Stephen Campbell Math & Computer Science Award"
    subtitle="Belmont University, 2021"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
      <li>
        Annual award recognizing outstanding achievement in mathematics and computer science
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Projects</div>
  </div>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="UnifyOps - Internal Developer Platform"
    subtitle="https://github.com/KominskyOrg/unifyops-core"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Designed and implemented a multi-environment Internal Developer Platform using Terraform,
        AWS EKS, and Argo CD to provide repeatable, self-service infrastructure
      </li>
      <li>
        Built full-stack application with FastAPI/PostgreSQL backend and React/TypeScript frontend
        featuring drag-and-drop infrastructure designer using Shadcn/ui and dnd-kit
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented Kubernetes abstractions including HPA, Pod Disruption Budgets, and scheduling
        constraints to improve platform reliability
      </li>
      <li>
        Developed GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines for build, test, security scanning, and
        environment-specific deployments
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Job Scanner - LLM Automation Pipeline"
    subtitle="https://github.com/KominskyOrg/job-scanner"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Built automated job screening pipeline leveraging GPT-4 for LLM-based role evaluation
        and fit scoring
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented LinkedIn scraping via Playwright with deterministic gates for dealbreakers
        and automated cover letter generation
      </li>
      <li>
        Designed full audit trail with prompt versioning, regression testing, and structured
        output validation
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Kominsky Auth Platform"
    subtitle="https://github.com/orgs/KominskyOrg/repositories?q=auth"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Built a containerized authentication service using Python, Docker, Helm, and Terraform
        with secure secrets management and JWT-based auth flows
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented microservices architecture with React/TypeScript frontend communicating
        through Flask API Gateway to backend services
      </li>
      <li>
        Docker images and Helm charts published to self-hosted Harbor registry, deployed to
        bare-metal Kubernetes with automated CI/CD
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Stack Templates - Microservice Scaffolding"
    subtitle="https://github.com/orgs/KominskyOrg/repositories?q=template"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Created production-ready microservice architecture templates implementing a three-tier
        pattern (App → API Gateway → Service)
      </li>
      <li>
        Each template includes Flask/React foundations, multi-environment Dockerfiles, and
        Terraform for Kubernetes deployment
      </li>
      <li>
        Pre-configured GitHub Actions CI/CD with Docker images and Helm charts publishing to
        self-hosted Harbor registry
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Python Core Package"
    subtitle="https://github.com/KominskyOrg/kom_python_core"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Developed foundational Python library providing standardized utilities across all
        organization microservices
      </li>
      <li>
        Includes HTTPClient for service-to-service communication, LoggingConfig with JSON
        formatting and rotating file handlers
      </li>
      <li>
        Typed API exceptions (ValidationError, AuthenticationError, DatabaseError) for
        consistent error handling
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Terraform Modules"
    subtitle="https://github.com/KominskyOrg/kom-tf-modules"
  >
    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Reusable Terraform modules for Kubernetes and database infrastructure consumed via
        Git refs for versioned, consistent patterns
      </li>
      <li>
        EKS module provides configurable Kubernetes Deployments with health probes, dynamic
        environment variables, and node selectors
      </li>
      <li>
        DB module integrates AWS Secrets Manager with Kubernetes secrets and Lambda-based
        database provisioning
      </li>
    </ul>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <TimeLineElement
    title="Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, Minor in Entrepreneurship"
    subtitle="Belmont University, Nashville, TN (Graduated Dec 2021)"
  >
    <div class="ml-4">
      <p><strong>GPA:</strong> 3.76</p>
      <p><strong>Honors:</strong> Stephen Campbell Math & Computer Science Award (annual awardee), Dean's List Fall 2019 - Fall 2020</p>
    </div>
  </TimeLineElement>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Core Skills</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10">
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Kubernetes & Container Orchestration:</span>
      EKS, HPA, Pod Disruption Budgets, multi-AZ scheduling, affinity rules, topology spread constraints
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Infrastructure as Code & GitOps:</span>
      Terraform, Helm, Argo CD, GitHub Actions
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Cloud Platforms & Architecture:</span>
      AWS (EKS, RDS, S3, CloudFront, Secrets Manager, IAM), multi-region, high availability
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Observability:</span>
      Datadog (APM, logging, metrics, distributed tracing), SLIs/SLOs, alerting strategies
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">CI/CD & Automation:</span>
      GitHub Actions, GitHub Actions Runner Controller, Docker, Harbor registry
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Programming & Scripting:</span>
      Python, Bash, Linux
    </div>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="font-semibold">Reliability Engineering:</span>
      Incident response, post-incident reviews, load testing (k6), capacity planning, cost optimization
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
